<!--
VOICING PLAN (4109 — Jesus Christ Is Risen Today, C major):
- Key: C major, no sharps/flats needed.
- Non-diatonic passing chords in bar 15 (B°, Bm) substituted with Am and Dm.
- Phrase 1 (1-4): Light and bright — open fifths in RH (E4-G4), ascending G-D5 in bar 1.
  - Bar 1: RH climbs from E4-G4 to D5-G5 tracking melody's C-E-G-C ascent.
  - Bar 3: RH sustained 2-note quarters under the running eighth melody.
  - Bar 4: RH C5-E5 half-note settled tonic close.
- Phrase 2 (5-8): More interior motion — F/C alternation in bar 5 with inner passing C5.
  - Bar 6: Dm7 resolved to C with dotted-quarter rhythm — variety in harp figuration.
  - Bar 7: LH adds Am and Dm to distinguish from bar 3.
- Phrase 3 (9-12): Development — higher register, G5 peaks in bars 9, 10, 11, 12.
  - Bar 10: RH E5-G5 at the e5 peak of the melody — climax of arrangement.
  - Bar 11: G5 sustained through three beats (bars 9-11 arc) for tension.
  - Bar 12: G7 color (B4-D5-F5) leading to dominant.
- Phrase 4 (13-16): Triumphant return + final close.
  - Bar 14: FΔ 4-note voicing (F-A-C-E) richest harmonic moment.
  - Bar 15: Diatonic wave (C-Am-F-Dm) with LH full 3-4 note chords.
  - Bar 16: Final C2-G2-C3-G3 in LH — resonant two-octave C major.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 1: RH E4-G4 → G4-C5 → D5-G5 parallel thirds ascending — bright Easter character.
- Bar 6: RH Dm7(F-A-C) → C(E-G-C) stepwise half-step F→E, A stays, C stays. Clean.
- Bar 9→10: RH peak — D5-G5 (bar 9 beat 3) → E5-G5 (bar 10 beat 3) — G5 sustained across.
- Bar 15→16: LH wave C-Am-F-Dm converges to C2-G2-C3-G3 for the broadest final resonance.
- Contrary motion: bars 10 (LH deep C2, RH high G5), bar 16 final close.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-4: Light and transparent — 2-note RH, 3-note LH, bright open voicings.
- Bars 5-8: Moderate — 2-3 note chords, inner voice movement, dotted rhythms.
- Bars 9-12: High and full — G5 climax, 4-note LH, stacks spanning two octaves.
- Bars 13-16: Triumphant — wide LH (C2-G3), high RH (G5), converging to deep resonant close.
-->
